A BILL ENTITLED
1 AN ACT concerning
2 Department of Commerce – Montgomery County Agricultural Reserve Study
3 MC 15–25
4 FOR the purpose of requiring the Department of Commerce to study the tourist and visitor
5 economy of the Montgomery County Agricultural Reserve and, on or before a certain
6 date, report its findings to the members of the Montgomery County Delegation to the
7 General Assembly; and generally relating to the Montgomery County Agricultural
8 Reserve.
9 Preamble
10 WHEREAS, There has been a consensus for decades in Montgomery County in
11 support of preserving the Montgomery County Agricultural Reserve, a large segment of
12 which is located in western Montgomery County; and
13 WHEREAS, The Montgomery County Agricultural Reserve was founded with the
14 principal goal of preserving open space and land for agriculture; and
15 WHEREAS, Farming remains the foundation of the Montgomery County
16 Agricultural Reserve and Montgomery County has established a Department of Agriculture
17 to help promote, support, and preserve farming and farmland; and
18 WHEREAS, The farming economy is a key focus of Montgomery County and its
19 Department of Agriculture and the farming economy is monitored and studied
20 continuously; and
21 WHEREAS, Outside of farming, a significant part of the land in the Montgomery
22 County Agricultural Reserve exists in the form of woodlands, open spaces, parks, historic
23 sites, and recreation areas of various kinds; and
