1 WHEREAS, Small nonprofit organizations and businesses are a major part of the
2 Montgomery County Agricultural Reserve and these organizations and businesses are
3 reliant on tourists and visitors, both locally and from throughout the Washington
4 metropolitan area, to support their operations; now, therefore,
5 SECTION 1. BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF MARYLAND,
6 That:
7 (a) The Department of Commerce shall study the tourist and visitor economy of
8 the Montgomery County Agricultural Reserve to develop:
9 (1) a deeper understanding of the tourist and visitor sector of the
10 Montgomery County Agricultural Reserve due to these sectors being not as well understood
11 as the agricultural sector of the reserve; and
12 (2) policies and recommendations to help the Montgomery County
13 Agricultural Reserve thrive.
14 (b) In conducting the study required under subsection (a) of this section, the
15 Department of Commerce shall:
16 (1) (i) establish a geofence around the Montgomery County
17 Agricultural Reserve and other key attractions in the area; and
18 (ii) use geolocation technology to gather information on visitor
19 volume and how those visitors interact with other parts of the regional economy;
20 (2) engage with visitors, including by surveying visitors, to gather
21 information about visitor behavior and attitudes;
22 (3) consider whether in–depth interviews with residents, businesses, and
23 other stakeholders are necessary; and
24 (4) review existing data models to gather information on the upstream and
25 downstream impacts of visitation to the region.
26 (c) The Department of Commerce may consult with government agencies,
27 academic institutions, and stakeholders to complete the study required under this section.
28 (d) (1) On or before June 30, 2026, the Department of Commerce shall report
29 the findings of the study required under this section, in accordance with § 2–1257 of the
30 State Government Article, to the members of the Montgomery County Delegation to the
31 General Assembly.
32 (2) In considering the data and its findings, the Department shall:

