1 (i) examine how tourists and visitors view the Montgomery County
2 Agricultural Reserve, including why they visit, where they came from, and what attractions
3 they found most compelling and why;
4 (ii) 1. identify the small businesses, recreation sites, and historic
5 sites that are located in the Montgomery County Agricultural Reserve; and
6 2. A. analyze how tourism and visitors contribute to
7 these operations and their success;
8 B. assess and evaluate the barriers that may deter visitors
9 from coming to the reserve; and
10 C. develop an overall assessment of the economic impact of
11 tourism in the reserve; and
12 (iii) make recommendations regarding policies and programs that
13 can help promote and preserve the Montgomery County Agricultural Reserve and better
14 support the small businesses, recreation sites, and historic sites that depend on the visitor
15 and tourist economy.
16 SECTION 2. AND BE IT FURTHER ENACTED, That this Act shall take effect July
17 1, 2025.

